Implementation for issue #10 Instead of checking out the commits to retrieve the modified source files, jgit ObjectLoader is now used. There are two main advantages: 1) Git checkout involves disk I/O, while jgit ObjectLoader just reads from .git This makes the process significantly faster. The 538 commit in our test oracle, used to be processed in 50 minutes with Git checkout, and now are processed in just 15 minutes. 2) Git checkout changes the head of the repository, which has to be restored, while jgit ObjectLoader leaves the repository intact. Added support for partially matching conditionals. When two conditional contain multiple sub-conditions separated with && or || operators matching one pair of sub-conditions is enough to match the conditionals. The developed solution supports the negation and reordering of sub-conditions, and accepts the replacement of || with && and == with !=

Improved further the detection of Move Attribute refactorings using information from the context: In particular, each Move Attribute candidate is assigned with a compatibility score based on: 1) The number of moved methods accessing the candidate moved attribute 2) The source class of the candidate moved attribute having a new field (after refactoring) with the type of the target class of the candidate moved attribute 3) The source class of the candidate moved attribute having a field (before and after refactoring) with the type of the target class of the candidate moved attribute The addition of the third condition eliminated 5 more false positives from the oracle.

Improved the detection of Move Attribute refactorings using information from the context: In particular, each Move Attribute candidate is assigned with a compatibility score based on: 1) The number of moved methods accessing the candidate moved attribute 2) The source class of the candidate moved attribute having a new field (after refactoring) with the type of the target class of the candidate moved attribute This approach eliminated 13 false positives in the oracle.
